SIMPLE: neglectful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neglectful
<hw>Neg*lect"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of neglect;
heedless; careless; negligent; inattentive; indifferent.</def>
<rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A cold and <qex>neglectful</qex> countenance.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though the Romans had no great genius for trade, yet they were not
entirely <qex>neglectful</qex> of it.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Neg*lect"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Neg*lect"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neglectingly</ent>⟦br⟧
